<big>Thanks for your support</big>

Core Linux receives support from its community and we would like to thank each collaborator for participating.

It is very easy to make a difference. Depending on your availability, you can help Core in one or more of the following ways:

<b>Support and Promotion</b>

<b>Spread the word</b>

If you like Core, let people know. Write a review and publish it. Talk about it with your friends and the people around you.

<b>Join the Community</b>

Core isn't just an operating system, it's also a community. We recommend you join the community and participate in making Core better.

<b>Project Contributions</b>

<b>Bug Reports</b>

If you've noticed something that doesn't work properly while using Core Linux, let us know. The problem you have discovered likely affects others too; The sooner we know about it, the sooner we can fix it.

<b>New Ideas</b>

The vast majority of improvements included in each release come from the community. If there's something you think is missing or could be done better, please tell us. Whether it's the inclusion of a missing hardware driver, or a software application that should be part of a stock installation, or if you have any other ideas on how to make Core better, we're always interested in hearing them.


<b>Art</b>

If you're talented in graphic design and willing to contribute to the project, please send us your creations and artwork. Whether it's a simple wallpaper, an icon set, a splash screen, or even a new logo, we're always interested in hearing about new artwork.

